You can install Acumatica ERP locally on a server, as described in this guide. ==Before You Proceed== Before you install Acumatica ERP, make sure that the server computer and software meet the system requirements, which are specified in [HelpRoot_Install\System_Requirements|System Requirements for Acumatica ERP 2019 R1]. ==Steps== [[#_142d1433-a8c8-447f-88aa-d4face758972|1. Install the Tools on the Server]{br}
[[#_15636f38-ddd1-422e-9bde-2d3b22be8af8|2. Deploy an Instance on the Server]{br}
[[#_ab17ccf0-5578-47ed-8385-a129363b85e2|3. Change the Password for the Default User]{br}
[[#_f3212bbb-90b3-4b6b-97de-9728855ac17b|4. Activate a License for the Instance][anchor|#_142d1433-a8c8-447f-88aa-d4face758972] ==1. Install the Acumatica ERP Tools on the Server== To install the Acumatica ERP Tools, you run the Acumatica ERP installation package and follow the instructions of the Acumatica ERP Installer wizard. (See the following screenshot.)[anchor|#_05137900-32b9-4b36-aabe-4b7d3450d752][anchor|#_7049124d-62d4-468d-8f58-fe4ce23dcdeb][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Installing_Locally_Step1.png|popup|300px] For details, see [HelpRoot_Install\Installing_ERP_Configuration_wizard|To Install the Acumatica ERP Tools].[anchor|#_15636f38-ddd1-422e-9bde-2d3b22be8af8] ==2. Deploy an Acumatica ERP Instance on the Server== You deploy an Acumatica ERP instance by using the Acumatica ERP Configuration Wizard, as shown in the following screenshot.[anchor|#_c4832844-f7cc-4cda-992b-4a109e8d1039][anchor|#_a10483c8-e41e-4b48-b604-4217401aa911][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Installing_Locally_Step2.png|popup|300px] For details, see [HelpRoot_Install\Installing_ERP_Instance|To Deploy an Acumatica ERP Instance].[anchor|#_ab17ccf0-5578-47ed-8385-a129363b85e2] ==3. Change the Password for the Default User== Every Acumatica ERP instance comes with an active default user account that you use to sign in to the system. After installation, you start working with Acumatica ERP by changing the password for the default user (see the following screenshot). You use the following initial credentials for the default user:[anchor|#_07bd13bb-3da5-4940-ae30-7f12b3eddfff] *User name: <tt>admin</tt> *Password: <tt>setup</tt> [anchor|#_93250d29-9f04-4d7c-8a6a-13a7a134c3a5][anchor|#_7acb0be9-0bc7-4ae1-8166-b79a66061d8a][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Installing_Locally_Step3.png|popup|450px] For details, see [HelpRoot_Install\Intalling_First_Start|To Change the Password at the First Sign-In].[anchor|#_f3212bbb-90b3-4b6b-97de-9728855ac17b] ==4. Activate a License for the Acumatica ERP Instance== On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_15_10|Activate License] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201510|SM201510]) form, you activate your Acumatica ERP instance by entering a product key. (See the following screenshot.)[anchor|#_4fad1a79-c2d1-43a6-a030-1ca458b7c77d][anchor|#_b23558e6-51a6-41fb-bc8c-d8e440099589][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Installing_Locally_Step4.png|popup|400px] For details, see [HelpRoot_Install\how__Licensing_ERP|To Activate the License for an Acumatica ERP Instance]. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_Install\Installing_ERP_Locally|Installing Acumatica ERP Locally] *[HelpRoot_Install\Licensing_Acumatica|Licensing and Activating Acumatica ERP]

In addition to deploying an Acumatica ERP instance, you can deploy Acumatica Self-Service Portal, where your customers can view all the relevant information about their interactions with your company and perform common activities online. In this guide, you will read about how to deploy Acumatica Self-Service Portal. ==Before You Proceed== Before you start deploying Self-Service Portal, you need to install Acumatica ERP and deploy an instance because its database is used by the portal. For details, see [HelpRoot_Install\Installing_Acumatica|Installing Acumatica ERP]. ==Steps== [[#_3baf824e-9665-4bb6-af15-4394a906855a|1. Deploy a Instance]{br}
[[#_947fb3b1-bc32-48db-aeeb-20057bb92018|2. Optional: Specify the Company Available for Users]{br}
[[#_f76e4233-9014-4e8b-ad14-8ae6f1f4226f|3. Activate a License for][anchor|#_3baf824e-9665-4bb6-af15-4394a906855a] ==1. Deploy a Self-Service Portal Instance== After you install the Acumatica ERP instance, you use the Acumatica ERP Configuration Wizard to deploy the Self-Service Portal instance and connect it to the database used by the Acumatica ERP instance. In the following screenshot, you can see the '''Create Portal''' check box, which you need to select on Step 6 of the Acumatica ERP Configuration Wizard.[anchor|#_bb9dc124-e144-4ccf-84c3-ec30057369c1][anchor|#_d08c2118-0bbc-47cb-bcfa-76ed8eb917fe][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Deploying_Portal_Step1.png|popup|300px] For details, see [HelpRoot_Install\Installing_Portal_Deploying|To Deploy a Self-Service Portal Instance].[anchor|#_947fb3b1-bc32-48db-aeeb-20057bb92018] ==2. Optional: Specify the Company Available for Self-Service Portal Users== If you use a multi-company Acumatica ERP configuration, after you deploy a Self-Service Portal instance, in the <tt>web.config</tt> file for the portal, you must specify the company that will be available for the Self-Service Portal users. (See the following screenshot.)[anchor|#_c1cdfb8c-3072-4d1a-a54c-66fdd0c44785][anchor|#_ed4a7460-d43a-48c1-bdb6-27d18ddbae2f][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Deploying_Portal_Step2.png|popup|300px] For details, see [HelpRoot_Install\Installing_Portal_Configuring|To Specify the Tenant Available for Self-Service Portal Users].[anchor|#_f76e4233-9014-4e8b-ad14-8ae6f1f4226f] ==3. Activate a License for Self-Service Portal== To use Self-Service Portal in production, you need to apply a license. If your license for Acumatica ERP provides you with a capability to launch the portal, you apply the same license on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_15_10|Activate License] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201510|SM201510]) form of Self-Service Portal. (See the following screenshot.)[anchor|#_e97c2669-d98c-4816-9678-13d55659f3c9][anchor|#_e051dd2f-f856-48b7-b8fd-3796eab9ea29][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Deploying_Portal_Step3.png|popup|400px] The instructions for activating the license are the same as those described in [HelpRoot_Install\how__Licensing_ERP|To Activate the License for an Acumatica ERP Instance], except that you perform these steps on Self-Service Portal. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_Install\Installing_Portal|Setting Up Acumatica Self-Service Portal] *[HelpRoot_Install\Licensing_Acumatica|Licensing and Activating Acumatica ERP]

You can run Acumatica ERP on Amazon Web Services (AWS). In this case, you use Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (Amazon EC2) to host the web server and Amazon Relational Database Service (Amazon RDS) to host the databases. In this guide, you will read about installing Acumatica ERP on AWS. ==Before You Begin== Before you start deploying Acumatica ERP on Amazon Web Services, you should do the following:[anchor|#ul_ngx_3d2_wl] *Sign up for Amazon Web Services. *Create a key pair, which you will need to get access to your Amazon EC2 instance. *Create a security group that will specify your Amazon EC2 instance and that can access your Amazon RDS instance. *Investigate the system requirements for the server computer and software and be sure they are met: [HelpRoot_Install\System_Requirements|System Requirements for Acumatica ERP 2019 R1]. *Investigate the recommended parameters of virtual machines: [HelpRoot_Install\System_Requirements_PCP_PCS_Licenses|Typical Hardware and Virtual Machine Configurations for PCS and PCP Licenses].
