You can use the Acumatica ERP web interface to remotely update Acumatica ERP (if it is installed in the private cloud or in the public cloud on Amazon EC2) to a newer version or build, as described in this guide.{br}{TOC}[anchor|#_e6d8ced4-f723-46a0-b6a6-23aeb66ae400] ==Before You Proceed== We strongly recommend that before you update Acumatica ERP to a newer product version, you do the following:[anchor|#_8d75e6ba-fa54-4dd3-9dce-af4ecf5fb1e7] *Back up all configuration files and databases used by the application instances. *If you have created any custom views with the {{SCHEMABINDING}} clause in the Acumatica ERP database, remove them. (You can create these views anew after update.) *If you have been replicating the Acumatica ERP database, turn off the replication. (Otherwise, the system cannot be updated.) *If you developed a client application by using the screen-based SOAP API, follow the procedure described in [HelpRoot_Install\Updating__how_Update_API_Using_Wrapper|To Update a Client Application that Uses Screen-Based Web Services] to prevent a failure of your application that can happen because of the UI changes in the system. *On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_50_30|Automation Schedule Statuses] ([~/?ScreenId=SM205030|SM205030]) form, make sure that no processes are scheduled for the update time. If you find any scheduled processes reschedule them so that they start after the update. *On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_35_20|Tenants] ([~/?ScreenId=SM203520|SM203520]) form, click '''Optimize Database''' to check your Acumatica ERP database for orphaned snapshots and delete them if the system finds any orphaned snapshots. [anchor|#_8b1d99a8-28ad-4222-9716-adea3b3ca93f] ==1. Lock Out the System== If users might attempt to log in to the system during the time of update, you need to schedule automatic lockout of the system on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_35_10|Apply Updates] ([~/?ScreenId=SM203510|SM203510]) form (see the following screenshot). You can specify the lockout time right before the update or several days or hours in advance (according to business processes accepted in your organization).[anchor|#_c2df2428-14dc-4836-949f-4a91c875a7e6][anchor|#_4127af0d-2554-4b12-b420-677557f1f905][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Web_System_Update_Step1_1.png|popup|300px]{br}
When the system is locked out, a message alerting users to the system lockout is displayed on the Welcome screen (as shown in the following screenshot).[anchor|#_61e3e920-a9b9-4736-8711-a7271d58b419][anchor|#_e14c5396-a0ee-4bf4-a8b4-c3432d436c01][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Web_System_Update_Step1_3.png|popup|300px]{br}
For details, see [HelpRoot_Install\Updating__how_Enable_Lockout|To Schedule the System Lockout].[anchor|#_6b5d7623-47cc-46e4-96f8-b4472064bf42] ==2. Validate Customization of Your Acumatica ERP Instance== If you have published customization projects in your Acumatica ERP instance, validate the compatibility of the currently published customization code with the code of the selected product version (see the following screenshot).[anchor|#_c96395fe-eab8-4bf2-b7a7-9dbfe4195fd4][anchor|#_2dad7c13-60b3-4ec6-893b-1bbaf5730bc7][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Web_System_Update_Step2.png|popup|450px]{br}
For details, see [HelpRoot_Dev_Customization\CG_GL_Upgrading_ValidatingBefore|To Validate the Compatibility of the Published Customization with a New Version Before an Upgrade].[anchor|#_20d4d536-b0ab-4eb3-b6ea-f746567bf70e] ==3. Update Your Acumatica ERP Instance== On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_35_10|Apply Updates] ([~/?ScreenId=SM203510|SM203510]) form, you update your Acumatica ERP instance (as shown in the following screenshot).[anchor|#_cd948235-7aee-4d9b-9b0a-11d5ef81bb51][anchor|#_5bc484c4-4d60-4d32-8652-e8b1b2f6e057][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Web_System_Update_Step3.png|popup|450px]{br}
For details, see [HelpRoot_Install\Upgrading_Using_Web_Interface|To Update Acumatica ERP by Using the Web Interface].[anchor|#_bbb5a380-e1db-41d0-962a-4787aa8a80ee] ==4. Build the Search Indexes== If you have updated your system from a version that did not include search indexes, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_95_00|Rebuild Full-Text Entity Index] ([~/?ScreenId=SM209500|SM209500]) form, you build the search indexes to accelerate search in Acumatica ERP (see the following screenshot).[anchor|#_40aa62d7-d04d-4dfb-a987-64d3e53b51c7][anchor|#_bbaed987-60bb-4a8a-98cd-41ed27fa6550][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Web_System_Update_Step4.png|popup|450px]{br}
For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SM__how_Search_indexes_update|To Build Search Indexes][anchor|#_c00630a2-d82c-47b2-9f2e-f9d35af1152a] ==5. Unlock the System== If you have locked out the system, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_35_10|Apply Updates] ([~/?ScreenId=SM203510|SM203510]) form, you unlock the system (as shown in the following screenshot).[anchor|#_5f9513b0-e4d4-4f08-b2a4-a01dd95b3532][anchor|#_deefbd99-b219-4304-a536-e27a37593d66][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Web_System_Update_Step5.png|popup|300px]{br}
For details, see [HelpRoot_Install\Updating__how_Disable_Lockout|To Unlock an Acumatica ERP Instance]. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_Install\Upgrading_Acumatica|Updating Acumatica ERP] *[HelpRoot_Install\Updates__con_Web_Interface|Updating Acumatica ERP by Using the Web Interface]

