You can update your Acumatica ERP Service on Windows Azure with a new installation package on the Windows Azure portal, as described in this guide.{br}{TOC}[anchor|#_94b158ac-2a00-45eb-9186-a5aa801aeedc]
==1. Download the Service Package File==
On the [http://partner.acumatica.com/|Partner Portal], you download the service package file (<tt>.cspkg</tt>) of the Acumatica ERP version to which you want to update your Acumatica ERP Service (see the following screenshot).[anchor|#_cd28d3fa-88ea-40cc-8b1c-28c009b72f52][anchor|#_e3da5fb4-99e1-4d13-a639-ab748119306a][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Azure_System_Update_Step1.png|popup|450px]{br}

For details, see [HelpRoot_Install\Deploying_on_Azure__Config_Package|To Download the Configuration Package].[anchor|#_6ab334a2-31a4-443d-898e-71b3a1ac385a]
==2. Download the Configuration File of Your Acumatica ERP Service==
You download the configuration file (<tt>.cscfg</tt>) of your Acumatica ERP Service from the Windows Azure portal (see the following screenshot).[anchor|#_d002cbc5-51aa-4466-aef2-f9d82b2e40dc][anchor|#_5751fa83-b373-4217-bae2-626901321665][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Azure_System_Update_Step2.png|popup|450px]{br}

For details, see [HelpRoot_Install\Upgrading_on_Azure_how_Download_Config_File|To Download the Acumatica ERP Service Configuration File].[anchor|#_5b8ef28c-8baf-4990-b681-2f5e0584ff19]
==3. Lock Out the System==
If users might attempt to log in to the system during the time of update, you need to schedule automatic lockout of the system on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_35_10|Apply Updates] ([~/?ScreenId=SM203510|SM203510]) form (see the following screenshot). You can specify the lockout time right before the update or several days or hours in advance (according to business processes accepted in your organization).[anchor|#_133e2a0f-b89a-40a4-957e-d1de7b0d209b][anchor|#_434ce2d8-c3a5-40d6-88c7-20b17cc34998][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Web_System_Update_Step1_1.png|popup|300px]{br}

When the system is locked out, a message alerting users to the system lockout is displayed on the Welcome screen (as shown in the following screenshot).[anchor|#_61e3e920-a9b9-4736-8711-a7271d58b419][anchor|#_e14c5396-a0ee-4bf4-a8b4-c3432d436c01][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Web_System_Update_Step1_3.png|popup|300px]{br}

For details, see [HelpRoot_Install\Updating__how_Enable_Lockout|To Schedule the System Lockout].[anchor|#_d32a41b2-59f6-4730-bcf9-0eb9e0f5dca3]
==4. Update Your Acumatica ERP Service on Windows Azure==
On the Windows Azure portal, you update your Acumatica ERP Service (see the following screenshot).[anchor|#_6826b424-0732-4007-8aa3-9d1ea299af49][anchor|#_d0e69a3a-2586-4e4d-b9da-a4258650ad9f][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Azure_System_Update_Step4.png|popup|450px]{br}

For details, see [HelpRoot_Install\Upgrading_on_Azure_how_Update_Service|To Update Your Acumatica ERP Service on Windows Azure].[anchor|#_4dd827eb-ad16-4914-8b45-e99f100ada2a]
==5. Build the Search Indexes==
If you have updated your system from a version that did not include search indexes, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_95_00|Rebuild Full-Text Entity Index] ([~/?ScreenId=SM209500|SM209500]) form in Acumatica ERP, you build these search indexes to accelerate search (see the following screenshot).[anchor|#_14d64a33-66fe-4609-bf76-8b2c4d4dbeb5][anchor|#_05d01ad5-05b1-400d-8c3a-7c19ce35d5a4][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Web_System_Update_Step4.png|popup|450px]{br}

For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SM__how_Search_indexes_update|To Build Search Indexes].[anchor|#_17124caa-c8a8-41a6-a4df-6669da5c08cb]
==6. Unlock the System==
If you have locked out the system, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_35_10|Apply Updates] ([~/?ScreenId=SM203510|SM203510]) form, you unlock the system (as shown in the following screenshot).[anchor|#_994201d9-1735-4dfd-88e3-f27554db53e9][anchor|#_7be1c167-c339-4af3-a071-645f01be5298][image:QuickGuides/Images/QG__Web_System_Update_Step5.png|popup|300px]{br}

For details, see [HelpRoot_Install\Updating__how_Disable_Lockout|To Unlock an Acumatica ERP Instance].
